org.mxupdate.plugin
Class GetVersion_mxJPO

java.lang.Object
  org.mxupdate.plugin.AbstractPlugin_mxJPO
      org.mxupdate.plugin.GetVersion_mxJPO

public class GetVersion_mxJPO
extends AbstractPlugin_mxJPO

The JPO class returns the current installed version of the MxUpdate Update deployment tool stored in MX. The JPO is used from the dispatcher class.

Method Detail

execute

String execute(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache,
               Map<String,Object> _arguments)
         throws Exception
Returns the current installed MxUpdate Update Tool version. The version itself is registered on the MX OOTB program with the MxUpdate application name.

Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache with the MX context
_arguments - arguments from the Eclipse Plug-In (not used)
Returns:
prepared return only with the version as string
Throws:
Exception - if version could not be evaluated

mxMain

@Deprecated
public void mxMain(matrix.db.Context _context,
                              String... _args)
            throws Exception
Deprecated. 

This is the main method called from MQL. The version is written to the MatrixWriter logger so that an execute of this JPO returns the related version information about the MxUpdate Update deployment tool.

Parameters:
_context - MX context for this request
_args - arguments from MQL console (not used)
Throws:
Exception - if the evaluate of the properties failed
